# Testing Patterns

## Integration Test Structure

Tests live in `test/tests/`. Each file covers one domain:

| File | Domain |
|------|--------|
| `extraction.rs` | Entity/relation extraction pipeline |
| `search.rs` | Hybrid search and RRF fusion |
| `storage.rs` | Repository CRUD operations |
| `temporal.rs` | Point-in-time queries, invalidation |
| `end_to_end.rs` | Full ingest → search round-trips |
| `multi_agent.rs` | Multi-agent and namespace isolation |

## Test Setup

Every integration test creates an in-memory SurrealDB instance:

```rust
let config = SurrealConfig { storage: StorageBackend::Memory, ..Default::default() };
let db = connect(&config).await?;
apply_schema(&db, &config).await?;
let repo = Repository::new(db);
```

Use `MockEmbedder`, `MockEntityExtractor`, `MockRelationExtractor` from core — no API keys needed.

## Assertions

- Search result order: assert the expected entity appears in top-N, not exact position
- Entity counts: use exact assertions after controlled ingestion
- Temporal: assert `valid_until` is `Some` after invalidation, `None` for active entities

## Running

```bash
cargo test                         # All workspace tests
cargo test -p context-keeper-test  # Integration tests only
cargo test -p context-keeper-core  # Unit tests in core
```
